cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.DC, cs.AR, cs.PL

This paper is about deploying deep learning applications, specifically focusing on GPU programming for DNN computations. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) since DNNs are commonly used in computer vision tasks. The paper also discusses metaprogramming and autotuning, which are related to programming languages and compilers, suggesting that cs.PL (Programming Languages) could also be a relevant category. Additionally, the paper mentions energy efficiency, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.AR (Architecture).
